[0] Requirements

 - Python
 - Numpy
 - netcdf4-python


[1] Set up

    Copy 0_setup.py to setup.py and edit. 
    Type:
        cp 0_setup.py setup.py 


[2] Prepare data files

    Make sure your aij data file exists at DATAFILE_DIR/XXXDATAFILE_TAG, 
    .R file at RFILE, and the consistent spectral file at SPECTRAL_FILE. 


[3] Execute

    Type:
        python main_directimaging_modelE.py

    The new directory to store the input parameters and the results is
    created in out/. If the directory already exists, you will be asked if
    you overwrite. 


[4] Done !

    